Subject: November 30 virus? (PC)

Early last summer, a Korean customer informed me that he had found
"November 30 virus" on our distribution disks, using a Korean virus
scanner.  Further investigation proved that he had infected the
INSTALL.EXE on the distribution disk upon running it, as our
distribution disks were not write-protected at that time.  He had
found several other PCs in his company were infected with this
"November 30 virus".

At that time, I was told by several regular contributors to comp.virus
whom I contacted by email that there was no known virus named November
30 or known to trigger on November 30.  In a recent Hoffman VSUM
database, There is now a listing for a Jerusalem variant with a
trigger date of November 30, discovered in January 1992.

Perhaps this was the "November 30 virus" found early last summer in
Korea.

