Date:    18 Mar 92 14:35:41 -0500
From:    "David.M.Chess" <CHESS@YKTVMV.BITNET>
Subject: TROI virus (PC)

A couple of people have mentioned that the TROI virus changes the
time/date of files that it infects.  While that's true of the version
that was sent to me, it's only because of the presence of a breakpoint
(INT 3, code CC) in the virus.  This was no doubt caused by someone
running the virus under DEBUG, and having a breakpoint set when the
virus copied itself.  Unless this was the original author, it means
that there's probably a version of the virus around without this bug.
The date-change is therefore probably not a reliable sign of the
virus, and people choosing signatures should be careful to avoid the
CC.  (The bug will cause files infected with this version of the virus
to malfunction in various ways, because the stack will be wrong; the
non-CC version of this virus will not have that problem.)

